"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105337","Department for International Trade","false","2019-04-02","<p>The ban on cat and dog fur as introduced by EU Regulation No 1523/2007 will be rolled over as part of the Withdrawal Act.</p><p>The Government has no plans to remove this ban once we leave the EU.</p>","Meon Valley","George Hollingbery",,"2019-04-02T16:14:02.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105337/answer","Biography information for Sir George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105337/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105337/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2019-03-26","Furs: Imports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what plans his Department has for imposing a ban on the importation of fur products.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","237099"
