the revenue of the victim surcharge in each year since 2013.","false","Biography information for Lord Ponsonby of Shulbrede",,"Lord Ponsonby of Shulbrede","HL14793"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104669","Home Office","false","2019-04-08","<p>The Home Office does not hold this information.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2019-04-08T15:19:11.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104669/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104669/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104669/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-03-25","High Rise Flats: Fires","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many high rise buildings retrofitted with combinations of composite or other forms of cladding which are not formed from solid metal along with phenolic foam insulation have had fires that resulted in fatalities in the last 10 years in the UK; and what estimate they have made of the number of such buildings internationally that have had fires resulting in fatalities in the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Lord Porter of Spalding",,"Lord Porter of Spalding","HL14794"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104670","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-04-08","<p>Development of digital technology and the digital economy is not specifically in scope of the Online Harms White Paper.</p><p>As part of the Digital Charter, the Government's overarching strategy to make sure the internet works for everyone - for citizens, businesses and society as a whole - we have already introduced a number of measures to protect the interests of the UK's Creative Industries, including facilitating a Code of Practice signed by search engines and copyright owners. This has reduced the prominence of websites hosting illegal copyright infringing content in natural search results.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde",,"2019-04-08T14:03:50.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104670/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104670/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104670/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-03-25","Copyright: Internet","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether the forthcoming White Paper on the development of digital technology and the digital economy will include reserve powers to address economic harm on online platforms in order to protect the interests of the UK’s creative industries against piracy and the spread of illegal content.","false","Biography information for Lord Smith of Finsbury",,"Lord Smith of Finsbury","HL14795"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104671","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-04-04","<p>We have made no such assessment. These are matters for Ofcom, the independent regulator.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde","HL14797","2019-04-04T11:32:42.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104671/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104671/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104671/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-03-25","Radio: Local Broadcasting","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the regulations issued by Ofcom in 2018 that allowed radio station owners to reduce the minimum amount of local programming on local radio stations during daytime hours from seven to three hours per day.","false","Biography information for Lord Storey",,"Lord Storey","HL14796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104672","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-04-04","<p>We have made no such assessment. These are matters for Ofcom, the independent regulator.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde","HL14796","2019-04-04T11:32:42.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104672/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104672/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104672/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-03-25","Radio: Local Broadcasting","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the impact on local communities of the decision by Ofcom to remove the requirement on local radio stations to produce their own breakfast show.","false","Biography information for Lord Storey",,"Lord Storey","HL14797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104673","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-04-04","<p>The Industrial Strategy sets out the Government’s ambition to make the UK a global centre for AI and data innovation and to embed the power of these technologies across our economy.</p><p>The estimate does not consider the potential job creation resulting from automation. World Economic Forum estimate that automation will create 133 million new globally by 2022.</p><p>The Government recognises that demand for skills will continue to change, in part in response to automation. In order to equip the UK to capitalise on this opportunity, we have committed to improving the UK's system for training in digital skills, lifelong learning to ensure that working people have the support they need to navigate the challenge of automation to a higher-wage future. The Government are investing £406 million in maths, digital and technical education and have committed £100 million for the first phase of developing the National Retraining Scheme to support people vulnerable to technological change.</p>",,"Lord Henley",,"2019-04-04T15:29:54.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104673/answer","Biography information for Lord Henley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104673/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104673/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-03-25","Automation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of reports that 1.5 million jobs could be lost due to increased automation.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Warwick",,"Lord Taylor of Warwick","HL14798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104674","Treasury","false","2019-04-08","The government is taking a proactive approach to support those in problem debt. First, the government has increased funding for publicly-funded debt advice to over £56 million in this financial year, enough to provide support to over 530,000 people. This advice helps vulnerable consumers to seek expert help with their debts and get their finances back on track.<p> </p><p>Second, the government is also implementing its manifesto commitment to introduce a breathing space and statutory debt repayment plan. The polices aim to give people in problem debt the opportunity to take control of their finances and put them on a sustainable footing.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2019-04-08T15:24:56.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104674/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104674/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104674/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-03-25","Debts","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what steps they are taking to improve measures to support those with problem debt.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Warwick",,"Lord Taylor of Warwick","HL14799"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104675","Department for International Trade","false","2019-04-02","<p>At last year’s Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting (CHOGM), hosted by the UK, leaders adopted a six-point Connectivity Agenda for Trade and Investment to boost intra-Commonwealth trade to $2 Trillion by 2030. As Chair-In-Office, the UK is committed to working with our Commonwealth partners to achieve this target. That is why at CHOGM we launched three new programmes aimed at promoting inclusive intra-Commonwealth trade, cooperation on meeting standards and promoting trade by women-owned businesses. The UK will also be chairing the Commonwealth Trade Ministers meeting in October.</p><p> </p><p>Of our 52 Commonwealth partners, 44 currently benefit from development-friendly preferential access to the UK market. The Government is committed to seeking continuity for our current trade and investment relationships as we leave the EU, including those with Commonwealth countries.</p>",,"Baroness Fairhead",,"2019-04-02T12:32:05.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104675/answer","Biography information for Baroness Fairhead","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104675/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104675/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2019-03-25","Overseas Trade: Commonwealth","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what steps they are taking to increase UK trade with Commonwealth countries after Brexit.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Warwick",,"Lord Taylor of Warwick","HL14800"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104676","Treasury","false","2019-04-08","The Government takes fraud extremely seriously and recognises the devastating impacts these crimes can have. The Government has created the Joint Fraud Taskforce, which brings together government, the banks and law enforcement to develop a collective response to fraud. The objectives of the Taskforce are to protect the public and businesses from fraud, reduce the impact of fraud on victims, and increase the disruption and prosecution of fraudsters.<p> </p>It has also been made easier to report fraud to law enforcement. Action Fraud is the UK’s reporting centre for fraud and cybercrime, providing a central point of contact for information about fraud and financially motivated internet crime.",,"Lord Bates",,"2019-04-08T15:36:49.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104676/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104676/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104676/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-03-25","Fraud","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what steps they are taking to work with banks to protect UK businesses against invoice fraud.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Warwick",,"Lord Taylor of Warwick","HL14801"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104677","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-04-03","<p>We continue to have strong concerns about reports of ill-treatment of Palestinian minors in Israeli military detention. We remain committed to working with Israel to secure improvements to the practices surrounding the treatment of Palestinians in Israeli detention, with a particular focus on minors. British ministers and officials continue to make repeated representations to the Israeli Government about detention practices. We advocate for the mandatory use of audio-visual recording of interrogations, a reduction in the use of single hand ties, alternatives to night arrests and for the Israeli authorities to inform more consistently detained children of their legal rights. We also continue to fund projects providing legal aid to minors and capacity building to local lawyers.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2019-04-03T16:08:43.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104677/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104677/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104677/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-25","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the number of Palestinian children who are, or have been, detained by Israeli forces in circumstances that break human rights and international laws; whether they intend to take action in response to that assessment; if so, what; and if not, why not.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL14802"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104678","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-04-08","<p>We have not raised this specific issue with the Israeli authorities. The British Government is very concerned at the high numbers of Palestinians killed by Israel Defense Forces in the West Bank and Gaza. We recognise the Israeli authorities' legitimate need to deploy security measures in some circumstances, but we have encouraged them to avoid excessive use of force and to act in a way which minimises tensions. When there have been accusations of excessive use of force, we have urged the Israeli authorities to conduct swift and transparent investigations. We continue to call on the Israeli Government to ease movement and access restrictions for Palestinians in the Occupied Palestinian Territories and to improve access to medical care. We are clear that medical staff should have the protection that allows them to do their jobs in safety.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2019-04-08T14:24:18.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104678/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104678/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104678/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-25","Yasser Fawzi Shweiki","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what representations they will make to the government of Israel about the killing of Yasser Fawzi Shweiki and reports that the Palestinian Red Crescent Society’s medics were prevented from attending the scene.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL14803"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104679","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-04-03","<p>While we have not made any representations on this specific matter, the UK has raised concerns over access to water in the Occupied Palestinian Territories with the Israeli authorities, including stressing the urgent need for Israel to take immediate and practical measures to improve the current situation and ensure fair distribution of water in the West Bank and Gaza. We have repeatedly made clear to the Israeli authorities our serious concern at the increase in demolitions of Palestinian properties in Area C of the West Bank and in East Jerusalem. We call on them to cease the policy of demolitions and provide a clear, transparent route to construction for Palestinians in Area C.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2019-04-03T14:45:18.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104679/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104679/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104679/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-25","Palestinians: Wells","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what representations they will make to the government of Israel about the demolition by Israeli forces of a water well in Umm Al-Nir.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL14804"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104680","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-04-03","<p>The right to education is a basic right, and every Israeli and Palestinian has the right to live in peace and security. That is why the UK continues to support education through our funding to the Palestinian Authority and the UN Relief and Works Agency for Palestinian refugees. Last year, UK support contributed towards the salaries of approximately 33,000 public servants under the Ministry of Education and Higher Education, including teachers, helping 25,000 young Palestinians to receive an education. We have repeatedly made clear to the Israeli authorities our serious concern at the increase in demolitions of Palestinian properties and we call on them to cease the policy of demolitions.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2019-04-03T15:10:20.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104680/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104680/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104680/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-25","Palestinians: Schools","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, following reports of the demolition of a school annex in Shufat Refugee Camp, what steps they will take to uphold the rights of Palestinian children to education.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL14805"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104681","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-04-03","<p>The fair and effective distribution of shared water resources across the Middle East is of great concern and we remain concerned about the quality and quantity of water available to residents of Gaza and the West Bank. We have made clear to Israel our ongoing concerns about its conduct of the occupation, including its impact on the distribution of natural resources. These resources are limited and therefore require the effective co-operation from all parties to manage them in such a manner that ensures there will be enough for all.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2019-04-03T16:00:09.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104681/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104681/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104681/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-25","Palestinians: Water Supply","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the statement by the UN Special Rapporteur for the situation of human rights in the Occupied Palestinian Territory, made on 18 March, that Israel is depriving Palestinians access to a regular supply of clean water.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL14806"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104682","Department for International Trade","false","2019-04-02","<p>The EU-Israel Trade Agreements and the transitioned UK-Israel Trade Agreement apply to the State of Israel. The UK has been clear that it does not recognise the Occupied Palestinian Territories (OPTs), including the settlements, as part of the State of Israel and that the OPTs are not covered by the UK-Israel Agreement.</p><p> </p><p>The EU-Palestinian Authority Interim Agreement and the transitioned UK-Palestinian Authority Interim Agreement apply to the territory of the West Bank and the Gaza Strip.</p><p> </p><p>Products produced in the Israeli settlements, located within the territories brought under Israeli administration since June 1967, are not entitled to benefit from preferential tariff treatment under either agreement.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Fairhead",,"2019-04-02T12:32:28.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104682/answer","Biography information for Baroness Fairhead","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104682/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104682/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2019-03-25","Imports: Israeli Settlements","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what trade agreements apply to goods coming from Israeli settlements (1) now, and (2) after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL14807"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104683","Home Office","false","2019-04-08","<p>The independent Commission for Countering Extremism’s study into the threat we face from extremism and the current response, including advice on new policies to tackle it, will report to the Home Secretary and be published shortly. The Government expects the Lead Commissioner’s report to include advice on the Commission’s future structures, work programme and, if necessary, the appointment of further commissioners.</p><p>Once the Commission’s has reported to the Home Secretary on its study and it’s been published, the Government’s response will be a decision for the Home Secretary.</p><p>The Commission for Countering Extremism’s public Charter is clear that it’s a transparent body operating independently of the Government. This independence extends to its decision about who it engages with and the methodologies and content of its reports.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford","HL14809 ; HL14810 ; HL14811 ; HL14812","2019-04-08T15:24:20.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104683/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104683/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1104683/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-03-25","Commission for Countering Extremism","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Statement by Baroness Williams of Trafford on 15 March 2018 (HLWS527), when the first annual report of the Commission for Countering Extremism is expected to be published.","false","Biography information for Baroness Warsi",,"Baroness Warsi","HL14808"
